Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Code interceptor not receiving callbacks

Solution: Ensure redirect URI matches exactly (including port)
Check firewall rules allow incoming connections on specified port
Verify the authorization URL includes correct redirect_uri parameter
Issue: Token exchange fails with invalid_grant error

Solution: Authorization codes expire quickly (typically 10 minutes)
Ensure code is exchanged immediately after capture
Verify redirect_uri in token request matches authorization request
Issue: Access token doesn't work with Graph API

Solution: Check token has required scopes for the endpoint
Verify token hasn't expired (check exp claim)
Ensure proper Authorization header format: "Bearer "
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated how OAuth misconfigurations in Azure SSO implementations can be exploited to gain unauthorized access. You learned to enumerate OAuth endpoints, exploit redirect URI validation weaknesses, intercept authorization codes, and exchange them for access tokens. You also created automation scripts to streamline the exploitation process.

Key takeaways:

OAuth security depends on proper redirect URI validation
Authorization codes must be protected during transmission
Scope configuration should follow least privilege principle
Defensive measures include strict validation, monitoring, and security controls
In production environments, always implement comprehensive OAuth security controls, regularly audit configurations, and monitor for suspicious activity. Understanding these attack vectors is essential for securing cloud-based authentication systems.

Remember: These techniques are for authorized security testing only. Unauthorized access to systems is illegal and unethical.
